// 6) Java Programming Exercise 

    // Q. Write program to calculate percentage of a given students in CBSE board exam. 
    //     His marks from 5 subjects must be taken as input from the keyboards.
    //     ( Marks are out of 100 )

import java.util.Scanner;

public class p_3 {
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("\nEnter Students Marks of 5 Subjects out of 100 : ");
        int a = sc.nextInt();
        int b = sc.nextInt();
        int c = sc.nextInt();
        int d = sc.nextInt();
        int e = sc.nextInt();

        System.out.println("The Percentage of the marks of the students is : "+(a+b+c+d+e)/5);
    }
}


Output :

Enter Students Marks of 5 Subjects out of 100 : 
78
85
98
67
56
The Percentage of the marks of the students is : 76
